OL,3,CTeen's life could have been saved if
OL,4,CScout leaders had given basic
OL,5,Cinstructions
OL,7,FBen and two friends had separated from
OL,8,Fthe other Scouts and were not
OL,9,Faccompanied by any of the three Scout
OL,10,Fleaders on the trip when he fell from
OL,11,Fthe cliff edge.
OL,13,FThe Scout Association for the first
OL,14,Ftime accepted responsibility for the
OL,15,Fdeath on the first day of the inquest,
OL,16,Ffive and a half years after he died.
