OL,3,CTeen's life could have been saved if
OL,4,CScout leaders had given basic
OL,5,Cinstructions
OL,7,FOn the day of Ben's death, he said he
OL,8,Flast saw the youngster who was with
OL,9,Ftwo other explorer Scouts in an area
OL,10,Fknown as Happy Valley on the way up to
OL,11,Fthe top of the Orme with most of the
OL,12,FScouts on a "meandering path".
OL,14,FSophie Cartwright KC, counsel to the
OL,15,Finquest, asked him if any instructions
OL,16,Fwere given or guidance or parameters
OL,17,Fset before the walk up the Orme.
OL,19,F"Not that I can recall," Mr Williams
OL,20,Fsaid, "I can't recall having any
OL,21,Fconcerns at all about the terrain."
