OL,3,CTeen's life could have been saved if
OL,4,CScout leaders had given basic
OL,5,Cinstructions
OL,7,FWhile on the walk, he received a call
OL,8,Ffrom another Scout Leader, Mary Carr,
OL,9,Fwho was ahead of him asking where Ben
OL,10,Fand his two friends were, but they
OL,11,Fwere not with him.
OL,13,FMr Williams then called Sean Glaister,
OL,14,Fthe most senior Scout leader on the
OL,15,Ftrip. He called one of the boys'
OL,16,Fmobiles, but they did not pick up and
OL,17,Fhe left a voicemail.
