OL,3,CTeen's life could have been saved if
OL,4,CScout leaders had given basic
OL,5,Cinstructions
OL,7,FMr Richmond continued: "There was an
OL,8,Fabsolute failure to demarcate safe and
OL,9,Funsafe areas.
OL,11,F"It was the most basic of
OL,12,Frequirements, that you identify for
OL,13,Fthese young people the boundaries
OL,14,Fbetween safe areas to walk and unsafe
OL,15,Fareas."
OL,17,FMr Williams replied: "Honestly, I, I
OL,18,Ffelt that the hazard was self-evident."
OL,20,FMr Richmond said: "But it plainly
OL,21,Fwasn't was it?"
